\[
\int_a^b \sin\left(\frac{x}{2} + 3\right) dx = 2 \cos\left(\frac{a}{2} + 3\right) - 2 \cos\left(\frac{b}{2} + 3\right)
\]
which is exactly the same as our result, because:
\[
F(b) - F(a) = -2 \cos\left(\frac{b}{2} + 3\right) + 2 \cos\left(\frac{a}{2} + 3\right) = 2 \cos\left(\frac{a}{2} + 3\right) - 2 \cos\left(\frac{b}{2} + 3\right).
\]

